author: Suhas Nayse
title: Nagpur's Rohan storms into U-15 State U-15 boys singles final
text:
NAGPUR: Rohan Gurbani stormed into the U-15 boys singles final in the Maharashtra Sub-Junior State Selection Badminton tournament at Ratnagiri on Saturday. 

In the semifinal, top seed Rohan ousted Rohan Thool of Thane 21-15, 21-13 to set up title clash against third seed Kedar Bhide of Pune. 

However, it was a heart-shattering three-game defeat for city duo of Sudhanshu Bhure and Jaskaran Suri in the U-15 boys doubles semifinal. 

After winning the opening game, the unseeded city pair lost 21-11, 16-21, 20-22 against top seeds Kedar Bhide and Parth Ghube.
